HEADWORD: Huskiness
<hw>Hus"ki*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
husky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Roughness of sound; harshness; hoarseness; <as>as,
<ex>huskiness</ex> of voice</as>.</def> <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

